TITLE: Defining Ethereum and Arbitrum Contracts in TypeScript for LayerZero
DESCRIPTION: Defines two contract configuration objects in TypeScript, representing Ethereum and Arbitrum LayerZero endpoints respectively. Each object uses a specified EndpointId enumeration and assigns a contract name string. These objects serve as references for building pathways between chains in the omnichain application configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/examples/oft-alt/README.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const ethereumContract: OmniPointHardhat = {
  eid: EndpointId.ETHEREUM_V2_MAINNET,
  contractName: "MyOFTAdapter",
};

const arbitrumContract: OmniPointHardhat = {
  eid: EndpointId.ARBITRUM_V2_MAINNET,
  contractName: "MyOFT",
};
```

