TITLE: Defining Contract Configurations for Ethereum and Arbitrum Using TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet sets up the contract details for Ethereum and Arbitrum networks, specifying network identifiers and contract names. These objects serve as the basis for establishing pathways and message configurations, ensuring correct network-linking for cross-chain interactions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/examples/view-pure-read/README.md#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
const ethereumContract: OmniPointHardhat = {
  eid: EndpointId.ETHEREUM_V2_MAINNET,
  contractName: "MyOAppRead",
};

const arbitrumContract: OmniPointHardhat = {
  eid: EndpointId.ARBITRUM_V2_MAINNET,
  contractName: "MyOAppRead",
};
```

