TITLE: Initializing LayerZero OApp Configuration (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This bash command initializes a `layerzero.config.ts` file for configuring cross-chain communication between OApps.  It sets up pathways between Hardhat networks with default LayerZero settings.  The task requires the contract name and file name as input parameters, which determine the contract identifier and config file name, respectively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/examples/oapp-read/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
npx hardhat lz:oapp-read:config:init --contract-name CONTRACT_NAME --oapp-config FILE_NAME
```

