TITLE: Filesystem Utilities - isDirectory Function in @layerzerolabs/io-devtools
DESCRIPTION: Checks whether a given path is a directory without throwing errors if the path does not exist. Returns true for directories, false for files, non-existent paths, or other filesystem entries. Requires Node.js filesystem modules and handles exceptions internally.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/packages/io-devtools/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function isDirectory(path) {
  try {
    const stat = fs.statSync(path);
    return stat.isDirectory();
  } catch (error) {
    return false;
  }
}
```

