TITLE: CLI Utility - promptToContinue Function with Custom Messages in @layerzerolabs/io-devtools
DESCRIPTION: Prompts the user with a yes/no question in the command line interface, awaiting a response. Supports custom message prompts and default responses, returning a boolean indicating user confirmation. Utilizes Node.js readline to handle input/output streams.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/packages/io-devtools/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
async function promptToContinue(message?: string, defaultValue: boolean = true): Promise<boolean> {
  const rl = readline.createInterface({ input: process.stdin, output: process.stdout });
  const promptMessage = message ? message + ' (yes/no): ' : 'Do you want to continue? (yes/no): ';
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    rl.question(promptMessage, (answer) => {
      rl.close();
      const normalized = answer.trim().toLowerCase();
      if (normalized === 'yes' || normalized === 'y') {
        resolve(true);
      } else if (normalized === 'no' || normalized === 'n') {
        resolve(false);
      } else {
        resolve(defaultValue);
      }
    });
  });
}
```

