TITLE: Filesystem Utilities - isReadable Function in @layerzerolabs/io-devtools
DESCRIPTION: Checks if a filesystem path is readable by the current user. Returns true if access is permitted; if the path does not exist or is inaccessible, returns false. Uses fs.accessSync with the fs.constants.R_OK flag for permission verification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/packages/io-devtools/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function isReadable(path) {
  try {
    fs.accessSync(path, fs.constants.R_OK);
    return true;
  } catch (error) {
    return false;
  }
}
```

