TITLE: Resolving Turbo Concurrency Issues in Bash
DESCRIPTION: This snippet addresses concurrency errors from Turbo when running the dev script using pnpm. It shows the error output indicating a persistent task count exceeding the configured concurrency, and provides the command to increase concurrency via a command-line flag. Required dependencies include pnpm and Turbo build tool. The input is a standard pnpm dev invocation, and output is successful execution without concurrency errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/layerzero-labs/devtools/blob/main/DEVELOPMENT.md#_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
- error preparing engine: Invalid persistent task configuration:
- You have 18 persistent tasks but `turbo` is configured for concurrency of 10. Set --concurrency to at least 19
```

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
pnpm dev --concurrency 19
```

